COMPONENT NAME: LKM SQL to SQL
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from any ISO-92 database to any ISO-92 compliant target database. - This module uses ODI Agent to read selected data from the database and write the result into the target temporary table created dynamically. - When using this module on a journalized source table, the Journaling table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface.
Restrictions: - This Knowledge Module is NOT RECOMMENDED when using LARGE VOLUMES. Other specific modules using Bulk utilities (SQL*LOADER, BULK INSERT...) or direct links (DBLINKS, Linked Servers...) are usually more efficient.
sedApta: - 20210525 (Davide Poggi): added sedApta CHAR semantics Task and SEDAPTA_CHAR_SEMANTICS option
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Create temporary tables with CHAR semantics
